Warnice  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Dębno, within Myślibórz County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  north of Dębno,  south-west of Myślibórz, and  south of the regional capital Szczecin.
The village has a population of 360.
